- The integer array parameter `customers` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `customers` length is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- The integer array parameter `customers` contains subarrays where the first element represents the arrival time of the customer and the second element represents the time needed to prepare the order.
- The arrival times in the integer array parameter `customers` are sorted in non-decreasing order.
- The chef prepares food for customers in the order they were given in the input.
- The average waiting time of all customers is returned as a double.
- The average waiting time is calculated by summing up the waiting times of each customer (finish time - arrival time) and dividing by the total number of customers.
- Solutions within 10^-5 from the actual answer are considered accepted.